text: Franklin County is a county in the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 17,097. The county has two county seats, Charleston and Ozark. The county was formed on December 19, 1837, and named for Benjamin Franklin, American statesman. == References == Category:Arkansas counties Category:1837 establishments in the United States Category:1830s establishments in Arkansas
title: Franklin County, Arkansas
